This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with image analysis and segmentation. The use of deep learning models and convolutional neural networks also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Additionally, the paper focuses on diabetic retinopathy (DR) grading, which is a medical imaging application, indicating that it could also belong to the medical imaging (cs.MED) and information retrieval (cs.IR) categories.
